            <marginalia hand="Italian">
                <language ident="LA">
                    <position place="tail" book_orientation="0">
                        <marginalia_text>Artes Legum, et Armorum: civili, militariq[ue] prudentia seri&ograve;, solideq[ue]
                        firmata[e]; et assidue magis, magisq[ue] propagata[e]. Nulla historia, tam industrijs fortibusq[ue]
                        actis, quam prudentibus consilijs, magis seria, atq[ue] solida. Nugarum pleni sunt pla[e]rique libri: Romani, Legibus, et Armis, facti sunt orbis Domini: nec vlla mundi Instrumenta hodie efficaciora, quam Justiniani Leges, et Ca[e]saris militia; 
                        antiquioris prudentia[e], fortitudinisq[ue] summa capita; et tot acrium seculorum pra[e]gnantissimi fructus. Hinc omnes Ciuiles, bellicaeq[ue] Controversia[e], accurat&egrave;, ac potenter composita[e]; semperq[ue] compondenda[e]. 
                        Soli fer&egrave; Romani, acres efficacesq[ue] mundi Actores; et in omni fortuna viri.
                        </marginalia_text>
                        <person name="Justinian"/>
                        <person name="Julius Caesar"/>
                    </position>
                </language>
                <translation>The arts of laws and of weapons were seriously and firmly strengthened with civil and military sagacity, and they were constantly propagated more and more. 
                    No History is more serious and solid through both diligent and courageous acts as well as wise plans. Most books are full of trifles. Romans became masters of the world by means of laws and weapons, 
                    and nowadays no means whatsoever are more effective than Justinian’s Laws and Caesar’s military campaigns, the top leaders of ancient sagacity and courage, and the fullest rewards of all those vehement ages. 
                    From this all civil and military conflicts were settled meticulously and effectively, and must always be settled. The Romans are almost the only keen and effective players in the world, and men in all circumstances.</translation>
            </marginalia>
            
